        "path": "/books/nahj-al-balagha:3:206:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/327/404",
        "text": [
          "۳۲۷. وَقَالَ (عليه ‏السلام): مَا ظَفِرَ مَنْ ظَفِرَ الْإِثْمُ بِهِ، وَالْغَالِبُ بِالشَّرِّ مَغْلُوبٌ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "327. Amīr al-mu’minīn, peace be upon him, said: He whom sin overpowers is not victorious, and he who secures victory by evil is (in fact) vanquished."
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
